<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis box="[199,411,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">External genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore with integument smooth, covered with somewhat dense short decumbent setae and sparse longer erect setae, with posterior margin slightly swollen and setose. Median apical process erect, approximately twice as tall as apical width, lateral margins converging from base to middle and remaining more or less parallel to apex, apex convex, margin clearly “hooked” or folded caudad, fold little wider than apex. Parameres moderately-sized, reaching median process at rest, more or less cylindrical but slightly sinuate at middle in dorsal plane, moderately setose except setae denser on dorsal margin and near apex.
</paragraph>
